  "editorial": {
    "headline": "Eli White Blasts Braves Past Mets in Critical Division Clash",
    "subheadline": "Atlanta Braves beats New York Mets.",
    "lead_angle": "Eli White launched a two-run shot into the left field seats in the eighth, breaking a deadlock and propelling the Atlanta Braves to a 3-1 victory over the New York Mets at Citi Field. The blast off New York pitcher Sean Manaea pushed Atlanta ahead for good, securing a crucial road win in this intense divisional clash.\n\nThe score stood knotted at one run apiece entering the eighth frame. New York starter Sean Manaea had surrendered a leadoff single to Ozzie Albies, who then moved to second on a groundout by Matt Olson. With two outs and a runner in scoring position, Eli White stepped to the plate, taking a pitch, then driving Manaea's 2-1 offering deep over the wall in left, silencing the home crowd and putting the Braves up by two.\n\nWhite’s heroics settled the contest, finishing the afternoon 3-for-4 with a home run and two runs batted in. Martín Pérez earned the victory for the Atlanta Braves, pitching seven strong innings, allowing just one run on four hits. Raisel Iglesias secured his eleventh save of the season. Sean Manaea took the loss for the New York Mets. This divisional showdown intensifies the standings, with Atlanta widening its lead over a key rival as the playoff race in the National League East heats up.",
